{
  "doc_id": "3898",
  "text": "Another known motif over-represented in this set of promoters was the abscisic acid responsive element (ABRE, [T/C]ACGTGGC) and ABRE-like ([C/G/T] ACGT[G/T][A/C]) motifs, which are a class of G-boxlike elements implicated in responses to abscisic acid and known to be recognized by bZIP proteins [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Two soybean transcripts homologous to the Arabidopsis HB-zip transcription factors ATHB2 and ATHB6 (see Supplemental Table 1 ) [CITATION_3] were found to be circadian clockregulated in seeds (peaking at CT4 or CT5). Th e known binding site for ATHB2 is, intriguingly, somewhat overrepresented in genes peaking at CT6 and CT11 (Fig. 6) .",
